cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY

The paper deals with neural architecture search, which is a subfield of machine learning. Specifically, it proposes a Bayesian approach to address issues with one-shot NAS methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the paper uses CIFAR-10 and ImageNet datasets. The paper also involves optimization and pruning techniques, which are relevant to sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a method for enforcing structural sparsity, which is related to sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
